label.value: Yellow Fever vaccine-associated viscerotropic disease AE

definition.value: A multi-organ failure AE that is associated with administration of a Yellow Fever vaccine. This happens when vaccine virus proliferates in multiple organs, causing multiple organ dysfunction syndrome or multiorgan failure and death.
A duodenal ulcer AE that alters GI function and requiresTPN indicated; elective operative or endoscopic intervention indicated; limiting self care ADL.
An anus AE that bleed from the anal region.
An anal hemorrhage AE that has moderate symptoms; medical intervention or minor cauterization indicated.
A thyroiditis AE where the thyroiditis inflammation has an acute process.
An anal hemorrhage AE that has transfusion, radiologic, endoscopic, or elective operative intervention indicated.
A gastrointestinal disorder AE that has a narrowing of the lumen of the colon.
A colonic stenosis AE that altered GI function.
A colonic stenosis AE that alters GI function and requires tube feeding or hospitalization.
An esophagus AE that has a rupture in the wall of the esophagus.
A mucosal inflammation AE that has moderate pain which is not interfering with oral intake but modified diet indicated.
A mucosal inflammation AE that is interfering with oral intake.
A dysesthesia AE that has burning or tingling sensation on the lips, tongue or entire mouth.
An oral dysesthesia AE that has disabling pain, requires tube feeding and TPN.
An oral dysesthesia AE that has m oderate pain and is interfering with oral intake.
An oral dysesthesia AE that has mild discomfort but is not interfering with oral intake.
A periodontal disease AE that has spontaneous bleeding, severe bone loss with or without tooth loss and osteonecrosis of maxilla or mandible.
A periodontal disease AE that has moderate gingival recession or gingivitis, multiple sites of bleeding on probing and moderate bone loss.
A periodontal disease AE that has gingival recession or gingivitis, limited bleeding on probing and mild local bone loss.
A necrosis AE that there the ecrotic process occurring in the rectal wall.
A rectal necrosis AE that requires tube feeding or TPN indicated; radiologic, endoscopic, or operative intervention indicated.
An inflammation AE that has inflammation of the salivary duct.

A salivary duct inflammation AE that has acute salivary gland necrosis; severe secretion-induced symptoms (e.g., thick saliva/oral secretions or gagging); tube feeding or TPN indicated; limiting self care ADL; disabling
A salivary duct inflammation AE that has thick, ropy, sticky saliva; markedly altered taste; alteration in diet indicated; secretion-induced symptoms; limiting instrumental ADL
A salivary duct inflammation AE that has slightly thickened saliva; slightly altered taste (e.g., metallic)
An inflammation AE that has  inflammation of the mucous membrane of the small intestine.
A small intestinal mucositis AE that has severe pain and is interfering with oral intake; tube feeding, TPN or hospitalization indicated.
A small intestine ulcer AE that has altered GI function, requires TPN indicated. Elective operative or endoscopic intervention indicated; limiting self care ADL; disablingoperative intervention
A small intestine ulcer AE that has altered GI function.
A tooth disorder AE that has a pathological process of the teeth occurring during tooth development.
A tooth development disorder AE that has maldevelopment with impairment not surgically correctable.
A tooth development disorder AE that has impairment correctable with oral surgery
A tooth development disorder AE that has hypoplasia of tooth or enamel.
A digestive system AE that has abdominal pain, fever, change in bowel habits with ileus and peritoneal signs.
A thyroiditis AE where the thyroiditis inflammation has a chronic process.
A chronic thyroiditis AE that shows a lot of dense fibrous tissue.
An acute thyroiditis AE that shows a form of painful, acute thyroiditis resulting from radioactive therapy to treat hyperthyroidism or from radiation to treat head and neck cancer or lymphoma.
An autoimmune thyroiditis AE where the thyroid gland is gradually destroyed.
An autoimmune thyroiditis AE that shows an organ-specific autoimmune disease characterized by thyroid autoantibodies, functional hypothyroidism, and absence of goiter.
A thyroiditis AE that occurs after pregnancy and may involve hyperthyroidism, hypothyroidism or the two sequentially.

An adverse event of hematoma in the subcapsular space of the kidney. This event occurs after a medical intervention, and may be caused by a tumor, trauma, vasculitis, renal infarction, or other disease process.
An adverse event of hematoma occurring around the kidney.
An adverse event of surgery that leads to the puncturing of an adjacent organ. For example, a needle to the kidney may puncture the adjacent organs.

A renal failure AE that is characterized by abnormally high levels of nitrogen-containing compounds (such as urea, creatinine, various body waste compounds, and other nitrogen-rich compounds) in the blood.
An adverse event with the IgA nephropathy, a form of glomerulonephritis (an inflammation of the glomeruli of the kidney), primarily characterized by deposition of the IgA antibody in the glomerulus.
An adverse event with the IgM nephropathy, a form of glomerulonephritis (an inflammation of the glomeruli of the kidney), primarily characterized by deposition of the IgM antibody in the glomerulus.
A urine abnormality AE that is characterized by dark colored urine resulting from abormally high blood levels of conjugated bilirubin.
A bladder cancer AE that is characterized by a benign or malignant, primary or metastatic neoplasm of the bladder.
A urine abnormality AE that is characterized by the presence of bile in urine.
